HEADWORD: Piddling
<hw>Pid"dling</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos><def>Trifling; trivial;
frivolous; paltry; -- applied to persons and things.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The ignoble hucksterage of <qex>piddling</qex> tithes.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Piddock</ent>⟦br⟧
